<paragraph id="9E2DEA5B346CFFEBFEC7C8ADFC6C447B" blockId="11.[264,1325,283,790]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Etymology. The specific name is in honor of Mr Luis E. Peña who made significant contributions to entomology and collected the 
<typeStatus id="412954F9346CFFEBFCD6CB45FC9D447B" box="[809,860,524,550]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E2DEA5B346CFFEBFEC7CB7DFC5C4413" blockId="11.[264,1325,283,790]" box="[312,925,564,590]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Variation. Ecuadorian specimens have darker coxae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E2DEA5B346CFFEBFEF7CB15FD2D454B" blockId="11.[264,1325,283,790]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Discussion. 
<taxonomicName id="599291D8346CFFEBFE66CB15FDC24428" box="[409,515,604,630]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penai">
<emphasis id="ACE63649346CFFEBFE66CB15FE704428" box="[409,433,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ACE63649346CFFEBFE3DCB15FDC24428" box="[450,515,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">penai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is apparently most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="599291D8346CFFEBFC94CB15FB6D442B" authority="Macquart" authorityName="Macquart" box="[875,1196,604,630]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="ACE63649346CFFEBFC94CB15FBDC4428" box="[875,1053,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry id="E685AACB346CFFEBFEB4CBCDFE5744C3" box="[331,406,644,670]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in that both have a rather short tergite 
<number id="285AF87C346CFFEBFC86CBCDFC4844C3" box="[889,905,644,670]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
, which is blunted in 
<taxonomicName id="599291D8346CFFEBFB74CBCDFB3744C0" box="[1163,1270,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penai">
<emphasis id="ACE63649346CFFEBFB74CBCDFB3744C0" box="[1163,1270,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. penai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and bears two distal clefts in 
<taxonomicName id="599291D8346CFFEBFDCBCBE5FD274498" box="[564,742,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="ACE63649346CFFEBFDCBCBE5FD274498" box="[564,742,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They differ in the shape of the male terminalia, mainly in the hypandrium, which is slender and without setae in 
<taxonomicName id="599291D8346CFFEBFBF7CB9DFBB044B0" box="[1032,1137,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penai">
<emphasis id="ACE63649346CFFEBFBF7CB9DFBB044B0" box="[1032,1137,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. penai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and broad with distinct posterior setae in 
<taxonomicName id="599291D8346CFFEBFDCACBB5FD254548" box="[565,740,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="ACE63649346CFFEBFDCACBB5FD254548" box="[565,740,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
